general_exclusion_criteria:
Severe cardiac comorbidity (congestive heart failure or cardiomyopathy with EF ≤50%);
Severe pulmonary comorbidity (DLCO ≤65 % predicted, FEV₁ ≤65 % predicted, resting dyspnea, or oxygen dependence);
ECOG performance status greater than 3 (except when attributable solely to disease);
Significant liver impairment (AST/ALT >5× ULN, alkaline phosphatase >5× ULN, bilirubin >3× ULN, unless explained by disease);
Renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance resulting in creatinine >1.5× ULN);
Corrected QT interval >480 ms;
Recent major surgery (<2 weeks);
Uncontrolled systemic infection;
Active uncontrolled cardiovascular disease (symptomatic NYHA III–IV heart failure, unstable angina, recent MI or stroke within 90 days, life‑threatening arrhythmia);
History of pulmonary arterial hypertension;
Clinically significant pleural effusion needing drainage;
Alcohol misuse requiring medical management;
Pancreatitis (active/chronic);
Known HIV infection;
Active hepatitis B or C infection;
Serious non‑study-related bleeding disorders;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Inability to swallow oral medication.

