Stage T4 prostate cancer by exam or imaging;
Baseline testosterone level > 50 ng/dL below institutional lower limit indicating profound hypo‑gonadism;
Active infectious process or chronic hepatic disease necessitating systemic therapy;
Human immunodeficiency virus infection with detectable viral load;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disease—including recent myocardial infarction (≤12 months), unstable angina, symptomatic pericarditis, NYHA class III–IV heart failure, recent major arterial interventions, or clinically significant arrhythmia within past year;
Uncontrolled hypertension;
Inability to orally ingest medications or gastrointestinal disorders markedly impairing drug absorption (e.g., inflammatory bowel disease flare, persistent nausea/vomiting/diarrhea, malabsorptive syndromes, extensive small‑bowel resections);
Known hypersensitivity to any investigational product components;
Documented non‑adherence to prescribed therapies;
Severe concurrent illness rendering the subject unsafe for surgery or study participation;
Concurrent administration of exogenous androgens, estrogen preparations, or fertility‑preserving hormones, or exposure to such agents within six months preceding randomisation;
Evidence of visceral metastatic disease (M1) on standard cross‑sectional imaging (computed tomography, bone scintigraphy).

History of significant cardiac disease (heart failure, myocardial infarction);
Uncontrolled hypertension;
Significant pulmonary disorders (history of interstitial lung disease/pneumonitis);
Severe hepatic impairment;
Renal insufficiency (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min);
Active untreated or progressing central nervous system metastases;
Concurrent serious infection (bacterial, fungal, viral) requiring systemic therapy;
Pregnancy or lactation;
Inadequate performance status (Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group >2);
Any concomitant anticancer therapy or participation in another interventional clinical trial.

