History of allergic reaction to gadolinium‑based intravenous contrast agents (not applicable if contrast is omitted);
Severe claustrophobia or anxiety preventing safe entry into an MRI scanner;
Inability to undergo magnetic resonance imaging;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illness including recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina, congestive heart failure New York Heart Association class III–IV, significant arrhythmia;
Baseline pulmonary toxicity or history of grade >2 pneumonitis;
Significant renal impairment (elevated serum creatinine or reduced glomerular filtration rate affecting ability to tolerate contrast when used);
Hepatobiliary insufficiency (bilirubin >1.5× ULN or transaminases >3× ULN);
Active central nervous system involvement or untreated/uncontrolled brain metastasis;
Known human immunodeficiency virus infection, chronic hepatitis B or C infections;
Concurrent participation in another investigational therapeutic study;
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Performance status greater than Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group 2.

