Pregnancy, lactation, or intention to become pregnant during study window;
Inability or unwillingness to employ approved contraception measures;
Live vaccinations administered within 30 days preceding enrolment;
Clinically significant cardiovascular disease occurring within 12 months (myocardial infarction, unstable angina, symptomatic heart failure, serious arrhythmia, peripheral artery disease grade ≥2, stroke, transient ischaemic attack);
Arterial thromboembolic event within 12 months;
Active Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection;
Hypersensitivity to the investigational product or its components;
Requirement for continuous therapeutic anticoagulation with vitamin K antagonists at baseline.

